```jsx
<Comp v-model={ foo.value } onUpdate:modelValue={ onUpdate } />
<Comp onUpdate:modelValue={ onUpdate } v-model={ foo.value } />
```

should compile to:
```js
{
  "onUpdate:modelValue": [($event) => foo.value = $event, onUpdate]
}
{
  "onUpdate:modelValue": [onUpdate, ($event) => foo.value = $event]
}
```

currently only the first one is used:
```js
{
  "onUpdate:modelValue": ($event) => foo.value = $event
}
{
  "onUpdate:modelValue": onUpdate
}
```

Same goes for `v-model:foo` and `onUpdate:foo`
